29:00.934 --> 29:03.567
Now--now,
DaVita denies wrongdoing.

29:03.567 --> 29:05.567
But they did settle that lawsuit

29:05.567 --> 29:08.734
for $389 million,
and remember that,

29:08.734 --> 29:10.533
because it's about
to become a theme.

29:10.533 --> 29:13.533
Because in 2012,
a former medical director

29:13.533 --> 29:16.100
at a DaVita facility
went public with claims

29:16.100 --> 29:18.700
about how DaVita treated
some of the medicine

29:18.700 --> 29:20.500
that it could charge
Medicare for.

29:20.500 --> 29:24.433
For instance, let's say, uh,
a patient needed 100 milligrams

29:24.433 --> 29:25.934
of a drug called Venofer.

29:25.934 --> 29:29.967
Uh, you could give them,
say, one 100-milligram vial,

29:29.967 --> 29:32.800
or you could do this.

29:32.800 --> 29:35.200
- What DaVita did--
instead of just one vial,

29:35.200 --> 29:38.600
they gave 50 milligram
out of this vial--

29:38.600 --> 29:40.867
residual trash.

29:40.867 --> 29:45.066
25, 75 to the trash.

29:45.066 --> 29:47.467
25 again, 75 to the trash.

29:47.467 --> 29:49.300
- The more vials DaVita used,

29:49.300 --> 29:52.233
the more DaVita was able
to bill the government.

29:52.233 --> 29:55.333
- Holy shit, that is
