35:23.367 --> 35:26.467
There's no bad decision here."

35:26.467 --> 35:28.533
And look, we focused on DaVita

35:28.533 --> 35:30.100
because they have
the most patients

35:30.100 --> 35:33.266
and Kent Thiry dresses
like an idiot all the time.

35:33.266 --> 35:36.333
But a lot of the problems
we've seen run throughout

35:36.333 --> 35:38.133
the for-profit
dialysis industry,

35:38.133 --> 35:40.800
including their main
competitor, Fresenius,

35:40.800 --> 35:44.333
who just last year agreed to
a $250 million settlement

35:44.333 --> 35:45.767
for thousands of lawsuits

35:45.767 --> 35:47.734
claiming that the company's
products had caused

35:47.734 --> 35:49.133
heart problems and deaths,

35:49.133 --> 35:51.600
claims that they deny,
because, you know,

35:51.600 --> 35:53.200
of course they do.

35:53.200 --> 35:54.667
So here's the thing.

35:54.667 --> 35:57.000
I know that all of this
has been very complicated.

35:57.000 --> 35:59.600
But there--there are actually
a few key lessons here.

35:59.600 --> 36:02.734
First, we need to make sure
that dialysis clinics

36:02.734 --> 36:04.033
have better oversight.

36:04.033 --> 36:06.233
And we need to create
better incentives

36:06.233 --> 36:09.467
for transplants and for
treating kidney disease earlier

36:09.467 --> 36:12.800
to keep patients out of dialysis
in the first place.

36:12.800 --> 36:14.400
And there are things
that everyone can do

36:14.400 --> 36:16.033
to combat the kidney shortage.

36:16.033 --> 36:19.500
Truly amazing people can donate
one of their own kidneys

36:19.500 --> 36:20.900
while they're still alive,

36:20.900 --> 36:23.300
and if you are someone
considering doing that,

36:23.300 --> 36:26.233
holy shit,
you're an amazing human being.

36:26.233 --> 36:29.300
Feel free to go
to giveandlive.us

36:29.300 --> 36:31.166
for more information on that.

36:31.166 --> 36:33.300
And for the rest of us
complete assholes,

36:33.300 --> 36:36.333
uh, we should at least--
at the very least--

36:36.333 --> 36:38.033
be organ donors when we die.

36:38.033 --> 36:39.900
'Cause organs can go to waste

36:39.900 --> 36:41.834
as families hesitate
to give approval

36:41.834 --> 36:43.200
when a loved one dies.

36:43.200 --> 36:45.100
So please, please make sure

36:45.100 --> 36:47.967
